WEBVTT

00:04.385 --> 00:07.548
Dr. Herman: I DON'T LIKE
QUESTIONS WITHOUT ANY ANSWERS,

00:07.548 --> 00:10.131
LIKE "WHERE DO WE GO
WHEN WE DIE?"

00:10.131 --> 00:13.134
I MEAN, I KNOW WHAT HAPPENS
PHYSIOLOGICALLY SPEAKING,

00:13.134 --> 00:15.136
BUT BEYOND THAT,
WHAT REALLY HAPPENS?

00:15.136 --> 00:16.347
ANYTHING?

00:16.347 --> 00:18.309
THAT'S WHAT YOU
START ASKING YOURSELF

00:18.309 --> 00:20.020
WHEN YOU LIVE
ON A CLOCK.

00:20.020 --> 00:23.023
ALL THESE QUESTIONS
WITHOUT ANY ANSWERS --

00:23.023 --> 00:25.406
THEY'LL DRIVE YOU NUTS.

00:25.406 --> 00:27.608
THAT'S WHY I LIKE
WHAT I DO --

00:27.608 --> 00:29.990
FIXING BABIES,
BIRTHING BABIES.

00:29.990 --> 00:32.363
NO AMBIGUITY THERE,
NO QUESTIONS,

00:32.363 --> 00:33.414
JUST ANSWERS --

00:33.414 --> 00:35.326
CLEAR, PRECISE,
OBVIOUS ANSWERS.

00:35.326 --> 00:38.459
AND LIFE --
BEAUTIFUL NEW LIFE.

00:38.459 --> 00:39.540
HOPE FOR THE FUTURE.

00:39.540 --> 00:41.041
GOD, I MISS THAT.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.083
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

00:42.083 --> 00:43.664
MORNING!

00:43.664 --> 00:46.877
ROBBINS,
ARE YOU EVER NOT CHIRPY?

00:46.877 --> 00:47.968
DOES THAT EVER HAPPEN?

00:47.968 --> 00:50.091
ARE YOU EVER
NOT SNARKY?

00:50.091 --> 00:51.132
ALSO, YOU SNORE.

00:51.132 --> 00:53.554
I-I CAN'T CRASH HERE AGAIN
TONIGHT WITHOUT EARPLUGS.

00:53.554 --> 00:55.476
OKAY, SO,
WE HAVE SEVEN CASES TODAY.

00:55.476 --> 00:57.057
THE FIRST ONE
IS IN TWO HOURS.

00:57.057 --> 00:59.019
ALSO, IT'S FRIDAY,
SO THAT'S MRI DAY.

00:59.019 --> 01:00.141
YOU KNOW THE DRILL.

01:00.141 --> 01:03.444
47 MINUTES OF MY
VERY LIMITED LIFE-SPAN WASTED.

01:03.444 --> 01:05.896
MM,
COME ON, COME ON.

01:05.896 --> 01:06.987
GOD! I'M COMING.

01:06.987 --> 01:09.190
STOP CHIRPING.
STOP SNARKING.

01:09.190 --> 01:12.153
WHEW! AFTER THIS, WE'VE
GOT THE DIAPHRAGMATIC
HERNIA. BABY'S 27 WEEKS.

01:12.153 --> 01:14.535
WE'LL DO A, UM,
TRACHEAL BALLOON OCCLUSION...
[ SIGHS ] HEY.

01:14.535 --> 01:17.458
FIGURED YOU COULD
USE THIS...
WHICH SHOULD, IF WE'RE LUCKY,
ENSURE THE BLOOD...

01:17.458 --> 01:20.411
...BEFORE
THE BIG LECTURE.
OH, UM, THANKS.

01:20.411 --> 01:22.002
THANK YOU.

01:22.002 --> 01:24.295
UM, THEY ALREADY SCHEDULED

01:24.295 --> 01:26.797
A FOLLOW-UP PROCEDURE
ON THE BABY, AS WELL.

01:26.797 --> 01:29.550
[ CONTINUES SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY ]
YOU'RE CULTIVATING
QUITE A BIT OF BUZZ, YOU KNOW?

01:29.550 --> 01:31.212
REALLY?
MM-HMM.

01:31.212 --> 01:34.054
I HEARD FROM TWO HOSPITALS
WANTING US TO RECORD YOUR TALK.

01:34.054 --> 01:37.097
[ SIGHS ]

01:37.097 --> 01:39.220
...BUT WE WON'T BE
TOO CLOSE TO THE DUE DATE.

01:39.220 --> 01:40.981
AND IF --
I HAVE A LOT
ON MY PLATE RIGHT NOW,

01:40.981 --> 01:44.145
JUST WITH, UH, HERMAN
AND HER TUMOR.

01:44.145 --> 01:45.606
UH, HER SURGERY.

01:45.606 --> 01:48.439
I REALLY NEED
TO FOCUS...

01:48.439 --> 01:49.690
ON THE TUMOR.

01:49.690 --> 01:53.284
DON'T NEED ANY DISTRACTIONS,
AND YOU'RE...

01:53.284 --> 01:55.286
VERY HARD TO IGNORE.

01:55.286 --> 01:56.947
HEY, I JU--
IT WAS JUST COFFEE.

01:56.947 --> 01:58.699
NO, I-I SO APPRECIATE
THE COFFEE.

01:58.699 --> 02:01.242
UH, I WAS JUST GETTING
SOME COFFEE FOR MYSELF, AND --

02:01.242 --> 02:02.503
IT'S GOOD COFFEE. IT --

02:02.503 --> 02:04.124
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT'S GREAT COFFEE.

02:04.124 --> 02:05.166
I-I, UH -- I CAN --

02:05.166 --> 02:07.127
I CAN JUST GET
MY OWN IF -- IF YOU --

02:07.127 --> 02:09.840
I MEAN, YOU CAN GET YOUR OWN
SO EASILY. [ CHUCKLES ]

02:09.840 --> 02:11.672
I-I DON'T WANT TO GET
MY OWN COFFEE. I -- [ SIGHS ]

02:11.672 --> 02:15.015
I MEAN [CHUCKLES] I DO.
I CAN. I WILL.

02:15.015 --> 02:17.308
I -- I CAN GET MY OWN COFFEE
ALL DAY LONG. I JUST --

02:17.308 --> 02:19.099
OWEN.
[ SIGHS ]

02:20.181 --> 02:23.063
THANK YOU FOR BRINGING ME
THE COFFEE.

02:23.063 --> 02:25.646
I REALLY LIKE IT.

02:25.646 --> 02:27.608
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:27.608 --> 02:28.729
UH, YOU'RE WELCOME.

02:28.729 --> 02:31.482
SO, HOW'S MY HEAD?

02:31.482 --> 02:34.074
THE TUMOR
SEEMS STABLE.

02:34.074 --> 02:35.776
I WAS WORRIED ABOUT
THE INFEROMEDIAL MARGIN,

02:35.776 --> 02:38.078
BUT THE GOOD NEWS IS,
THERE'S NO SIGN OF GROWTH.

02:38.078 --> 02:40.080
IT HASN'T INVADED
THE OPTIC NERVE YET.

02:40.080 --> 02:41.622
WELL, HOW LONG
TILL IT DOES?

02:41.622 --> 02:43.954
I NEED A NUMBER, SHEPHERD.
I HAVE THINGS TO PLAN.

02:43.954 --> 02:45.916
ABOUT SIX WEEKS --
MAYBE EIGHT

02:45.916 --> 02:47.628
IF YOU GO IN FOR THE
LOCALIZED RADIATION TREATMENTS

02:47.628 --> 02:48.789
I'VE PRESCRIBED FOR YOU.

02:48.789 --> 02:50.381
I'D LIKE
FOR THOSE TO START TODAY.

02:50.381 --> 02:51.131
NO, NO, NO, NO.

02:51.131 --> 02:52.553
I TRIED THAT.
HATED IT.

02:52.553 --> 02:54.675
DOCTOR'S ORDERS.
IT IS OUR BEST CHANCE

02:54.675 --> 02:57.007
TO SHRINK THE PART OF
THE TUMOR ON YOUR OPTIC CHIASM.

02:57.007 --> 02:58.469
OH, CRAP.
Miranda:
GLENDA CASTILLO!

02:58.469 --> 02:59.680
WE'RE HEADED TO SURGERY,
DR. BAILEY.

02:59.680 --> 03:00.851
NO TIME TO TALK.

03:00.851 --> 03:02.012
BUT YOU HAVEN'T
GIVEN ME AN ANSWER.

03:02.012 --> 03:03.304
ACTUALLY, I HAVE.
IT WAS NO.

03:03.304 --> 03:04.765
BUT YOU HAVEN'T GIVEN ME
THE RIGHT ANSWER.

03:04.765 --> 03:06.066
YOU COULD AT LEAST
MEET WITH HER.

03:06.066 --> 03:07.268
I'VE SEEN THE CASE,
OKAY?

03:07.268 --> 03:08.519
I-I'M SORRY,

03:08.519 --> 03:10.361
BUT I'M WORKING ON
A VERY LIMITED TIME FRAME

03:10.361 --> 03:13.444
WITH A VERY SPECIFIC LIST
OF SURGERIES TO TEACH ROBBINS,

03:13.444 --> 03:14.985
AND GLENDA CASTILLO
ISN'T ONE OF THEM.

03:14.985 --> 03:17.698
OKAY, WELL, AS A PERSONAL FAVOR
TO ME, JUST ME PER--

03:17.698 --> 03:19.870
I HAVE NO TIME
TO MAKE IT PERSONAL.

03:19.870 --> 03:21.201
IT'S A NO.
I'M SORRY.

03:21.201 --> 03:22.913
I'LL GET YOU SOME NAMES --
GOOD PEOPLE.

03:22.913 --> 03:24.164
SHE CAN SEE
ONE OF THEM.

03:26.086 --> 03:27.958
UM, SORRY.

03:33.093 --> 03:35.095
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

03:43.684 --> 03:46.226
THREE DOWN,
ALL THESE TO GO.

03:46.226 --> 03:48.148
Arizona: WE'VE GOT FOUR MONTHS'
WORTH OF SURGERIES UP HERE.

03:48.148 --> 03:51.061
I MEAN, HOW ARE WE GONNA
GET FOUR MONTHS OF SURGERIES
DONE IN EIGHT WEEKS?

03:51.061 --> 03:53.193
WE JUST DO, I SUPPOSE.

03:53.193 --> 03:54.905
YOU'LL DO THE NEXT ONE YOURSELF.
I'LL WATCH.

03:54.905 --> 03:55.906
WHAT?

03:55.906 --> 03:57.027
NO. NO, THANK YOU.

03:57.027 --> 03:58.028
I APPRECIATE
THE VOTE OF CONFIDENCE,

03:58.028 --> 03:59.700
BUT I'M NOT EVEN ACTUALLY SURE
THAT I KNOW HOW --

03:59.700 --> 04:01.412
I NEED TO SEE
WHAT YOU'VE LEARNED,

04:01.412 --> 04:03.534
WHAT YOU CAN AND CAN'T DO
ON YOUR OWN

04:03.534 --> 04:06.367
WHILE I'M STILL AROUND
TO FIX IT WHEN YOU SCREW UP.

04:06.367 --> 04:07.788
GEE, THANKS.

04:07.788 --> 04:09.630
IT'S NOT A VOTE OF CONFIDENCE.
IT'S A NECESSITY.

04:09.630 --> 04:11.171
TRAINING WHEELS ARE OFF,
ROBBINS.

04:11.171 --> 04:12.042
TIME IS UP.
WHAT'S NEXT?

04:12.042 --> 04:13.874
UH, YOUR
RADIATION TREATMENT.

04:13.874 --> 04:14.755
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
UGH.

04:14.755 --> 04:16.006
RADIATION
HASN'T WORKED YET.

04:16.006 --> 04:18.839
I DON'T SEE WHY IT'S SUDDENLY
SUPPOSED TO START WORKING.

04:18.839 --> 04:19.970
RADIATION IS BULL--

04:19.970 --> 04:21.802
SHEPHERD SAYS
THAT IT'S NECESSARY.

04:21.802 --> 04:23.884
SHE'S THE DOCTOR HERE.

04:23.884 --> 04:27.147
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

04:27.147 --> 04:28.188
[ CONVERSATIONS STOP ]

04:30.391 --> 04:32.603
"LIFE WILL OUT."

04:32.603 --> 04:35.946
THE ORIGINS AND LESSONS
OF LIFE AND EVOLUTION

04:35.946 --> 04:37.448
ARE LONG AND COMPLEX,

04:37.448 --> 04:42.072
BUT WHAT THEY BASICALLY
BOIL DOWN TO IS, LIFE WILL OUT.

04:42.072 --> 04:45.075
LIFE WILL ALWAYS
FIND A WAY TO CONTINUE.

04:45.075 --> 04:46.206
ALWAYS.

04:46.206 --> 04:49.209
LIFE...WILL...OUT.

04:50.871 --> 04:54.585
THIS IS A MASSIVE
GRADE IV ASTROCYTOMA.

04:54.585 --> 04:56.587
I WANT YOU
TO TAKE A LOOK AT IT.

04:56.587 --> 04:58.679
REALLY LOOK.

04:58.679 --> 05:00.511
LOOK AT ITS SIZE.

05:00.511 --> 05:03.133
LOOK AT THE WAY
IT INVADES HEALTHY TISSUE.

05:03.133 --> 05:05.265
LOOK AT ITS VASCULATURE.

05:05.265 --> 05:10.020
IT IS BLOOD AND TISSUE
AND FLESH.

05:10.020 --> 05:11.311
IT'S GROWING...
[ MONITOR BEEPS ]

05:11.311 --> 05:13.354
...ADAPTING
TO ITS ENVIRONMENT,

05:13.354 --> 05:16.857
STRUGGLING TO SURVIVE,
TO STAY ALIVE.

05:16.857 --> 05:18.238
IT IS ALIVE.

05:18.238 --> 05:19.900
WE DON'T LIKE
TO THINK OF IT THAT WAY,

05:19.900 --> 05:23.113
BUT IT'S NESTED IN THE WOMB
OF A HUMAN BRAIN,

05:23.113 --> 05:27.117
FEEDING ON ITS HOST,
GROWING AND FIGHTING FOR LIFE --

05:27.117 --> 05:28.539
ALMOST LIKE A FETUS.

05:28.539 --> 05:29.910
NO, SCRATCH THAT.

05:29.910 --> 05:31.952
LET'S JUST
FOR SCIENCE AND GIGGLES

05:31.952 --> 05:33.253
SAY EXACTLY LIKE A FETUS.

05:33.253 --> 05:36.507
BECAUSE LIKE A HEALTHY FETUS,
IT IS THRIVING.

05:36.507 --> 05:39.049
YOU KNOW, THERE ARE EVEN
SOME TYPES OF TUMORS

05:39.049 --> 05:41.422
THAT GROW TEETH, HAIR...
[ AUDIENCE MURMURS ]

05:41.422 --> 05:43.964
...A STRAY EYE.
[ AUDIENCE GROANS LOUDLY ]

05:43.964 --> 05:45.516
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:45.516 --> 05:47.137
HAVE I REPULSED YOU?

05:47.137 --> 05:49.309
IT'S GROSS, RIGHT?
Woman: YEAH.

05:49.309 --> 05:51.852
I MEAN, THAT IS A PROBLEM.
[ SIGHS ]

05:51.852 --> 05:54.645
NOBODY WANTS SOMETHING
THAT NASTY IN THEIR HEAD.

05:54.645 --> 05:59.029
I'D LIKE YOU FOR ONE MOMENT
TO CONSIDER THE IDEA

05:59.029 --> 06:03.444
THAT, TO THE TUMOR,
WE ARE THE PROBLEM,

06:03.444 --> 06:04.985
WE ARE THE INVADER.

06:04.985 --> 06:06.657
WE ARE THE DANGER.

06:06.657 --> 06:09.540
TO THE TUMOR,
WE ARE THE CANCER.

06:09.540 --> 06:11.702
AND THE TUMOR?

06:11.702 --> 06:15.375
WELL, THE TUMOR SEES ITSELF AS
A SWEET, CUTE, FAT-CHEEKED BABY

06:15.375 --> 06:17.498
JUST TRYING TO MAKE ITS WAY
INTO THE WORLD,

06:17.498 --> 06:20.340
AND WE WANT TO STOP IT,
DESTROY IT,

06:20.340 --> 06:24.304
TEAR IT FROM ITS HAPPY
LITTLE HOME LIKE BARBARIANS.

06:24.304 --> 06:26.176
TO THE TUMOR,

06:26.176 --> 06:29.139
WE ARE THE SOULLESS,
MURDEROUS MONSTERS.

06:29.139 --> 06:31.391
WHY DO I DO THIS?

06:31.391 --> 06:35.105
WHY DO I CALL IT "BABY"
AND TALK ABOUT KILLING IT?

06:35.105 --> 06:37.978
BECAUSE THIS KIND OF TUMOR
DESERVES RESPECT.

06:39.399 --> 06:41.321
IT DESERVES
A LITTLE HUMANITY.

06:41.321 --> 06:44.024
CHARMING, ISN'T IT?

06:44.024 --> 06:46.156
THEY PUT CLOUDS ON THE CEILING
TO DISTRACT YOU.

06:46.156 --> 06:49.119
LEAST THEY COULD DO IS PUT
SOMETHING INTERESTING UP THERE,

06:49.119 --> 06:50.370
LIKE PORN.

06:50.370 --> 06:52.533
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:52.533 --> 06:53.373
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

06:53.373 --> 06:56.336
IT'S NOT JUST A TUMOR.

06:56.336 --> 06:57.958
IT'S INGENUITY.

06:57.958 --> 06:59.089
IT'S STRENGTH.

06:59.089 --> 07:00.881
IT'S ADAPTABILITY.

07:00.881 --> 07:03.133
IT'S POETRY.

07:03.133 --> 07:05.596
IT'S ONE OF GOD'S
MASTERPIECES.

07:05.596 --> 07:09.349
IT IS ALIVE.

07:14.685 --> 07:15.896
MM.

07:17.478 --> 07:18.859
[ CLIPS FASTENING ]

07:21.692 --> 07:23.614
[ BREATHING RAPIDLY ]

07:26.026 --> 07:27.778
You okay?

07:27.778 --> 07:30.450
SURE.

07:30.450 --> 07:33.243
AND LIKE ANY LIVING THING,
IT WANTS TO STAY ALIVE.

07:33.243 --> 07:34.785
LIKE ANY LIVING THING,

07:34.785 --> 07:37.167
IT IS GOING TO FIGHT LIKE HELL
TO SURVIVE.

07:37.167 --> 07:40.380
AND WHEN I SAW OPEN THAT SKULL
AND COME FACE-TO-FACE WITH IT,

07:40.380 --> 07:43.213
WITH THAT TUMOR,
WITH THAT LIVING THING,

07:43.213 --> 07:45.716
IT WILL BE
ALMOST IMPOSSIBLE TO REMOVE...

07:45.716 --> 07:47.217
WELL, I'LL SEE YOU AFTER.

07:50.050 --> 07:52.973
...BECAUSE IT WOULD RATHER
DESTROY THE BRAIN THAT HOLDS IT

07:52.973 --> 07:55.475
THAN GO GENTLY
INTO THAT GOOD NIGHT.

07:55.475 --> 07:57.808
[ BREATHING DEEPLY ]

08:12.162 --> 08:14.164
IT IS ALIVE.

08:16.286 --> 08:18.999
AND WHAT'S IT ALL
COME DOWN TO?

08:18.999 --> 08:20.290
LIFE...

08:20.290 --> 08:22.002
WILL...

08:22.002 --> 08:25.005
OUT.

08:39.189 --> 08:43.694
Amelia:
SO, OUR FAT-CHEEKED-BABY TUMOR

08:43.694 --> 08:45.275
THAT'S NESTLED
IN THAT BRAIN,

08:45.275 --> 08:46.857
IT'S A CREATURE OF HABIT.

08:46.857 --> 08:50.701
IT HAS THE SAME ROUTINE
DAY IN AND DAY OUT --

08:50.701 --> 08:54.154
TO GROW, TO SPREAD OUT,
TO TAKE UP SPACE.

08:54.154 --> 08:55.956
[ MACHINE BEEPS, WHIRS ]
THAT'S IT.

08:55.956 --> 09:02.422
AT THIS POINT, OUR BABY TUMOR
IS SO ENMESHED, SO INVASIVE,

09:02.422 --> 09:05.005
IT'S TOUCHING VIRTUALLY
EVERY SINGLE BRAIN STRUCTURE.

09:05.005 --> 09:06.797
IT'S PUSHED
EXISTING TISSUE ASIDE,

09:06.797 --> 09:10.010
SHOVED BRAIN MATTER OUT OF
THE WAY TO FIND ROOM FOR ITSELF.

09:10.010 --> 09:15.385
HOW DO YOU REMOVE IT WITHOUT
DESTROYING THE BRAIN AROUND IT?

09:15.385 --> 09:18.098
HOW DO YOU KILL THE BABY
WITHOUT KILLING THE MOTHER?

09:19.349 --> 09:24.234
I STARE AT THESE SCANS,
AND THE TUMOR STARES BACK AT ME,

09:24.234 --> 09:27.147
DARING ME
TO TRY TO EXTRACT IT.

09:27.147 --> 09:29.780
I MEAN, THIS TUMOR
IS BOLD AND BRAZEN.

09:29.780 --> 09:31.151
THIS TUMOR
THINKS IT'S IN CHARGE.

09:31.151 --> 09:33.994
THIS TUMOR
THINKS IT OWNS THE PLACE.

09:33.994 --> 09:35.575
I DON'T HAVE TO
EXPLAIN MYSELF TO YOU.

09:35.575 --> 09:37.327
YOU MISSED YOUR RADIATION
SESSION THIS MORNING.

09:37.327 --> 09:39.249
I TOLD YOU,
I'M NOT DOING THAT ANYMORE.

09:39.249 --> 09:40.661
THAT IS NOT YOUR CALL.

09:40.661 --> 09:43.373
MY TUMOR, MY HEAD --
IT ABSOLUTELY IS MY CALL.

09:43.373 --> 09:46.046
THE TUMOR WILL BE
EXPONENTIALLY EASIER TO REMOVE

09:46.046 --> 09:47.207
AFTER THE RADIATION.

09:47.207 --> 09:49.129
NICOLE, PLEASE.

09:49.129 --> 09:50.671
GO TO RADIATION!

09:50.671 --> 09:52.212
I WILL THINK ABOUT IT.

09:52.212 --> 09:53.383
O-KAY.

09:53.383 --> 09:55.095
THE THING ABOUT
A TUMOR LIKE THIS IS,

09:55.095 --> 09:57.217
YOU CAN'T
LET IT INTIMIDATE YOU.

09:57.217 --> 09:59.890
THE TUMOR
ISN'T SMARTER THAN YOU.

09:59.890 --> 10:02.432
YOU JUST NEED
A PLAN OF ATTACK.
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

10:02.432 --> 10:03.523
Dr. Herman:
HERE. FEEL THAT?

10:03.523 --> 10:05.225
YOU MUST BE METHODICAL.

10:05.225 --> 10:07.187
YOU WANT TO FIND A
SPOT WITH JUST THE
RIGHT AMOUNT OF GIVE.

10:07.187 --> 10:08.358
THAT'S WHERE
YOU WANT TO CUT.

10:08.358 --> 10:09.149
SCALPEL.

10:09.149 --> 10:10.821
POINT OF ACCESS IS KEY.

10:10.821 --> 10:11.942
YOU'RE UP, ROBBINS.

10:11.942 --> 10:13.033
Arizona: I KNOW.

10:13.033 --> 10:14.194
I'VE NEVER DONE
THAT PART BEFORE.

10:14.194 --> 10:16.997
SO, UM, YOU WERE
REALLY SERIOUS ABOUT THAT?

10:16.997 --> 10:18.038
IT'S TIME.
MAKE THE CUT.

10:18.038 --> 10:19.579
BUT I DON'T KNOW --
I'VE NEVER --

10:19.579 --> 10:21.161
MAKE THE CUT.

10:24.124 --> 10:25.085
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

10:29.209 --> 10:30.961
AND THEN YOU START.

10:33.053 --> 10:36.677
THAT IS
THE MOST DAUNTING STEP --

10:36.677 --> 10:42.062
PUSHING A BLADE INTO THAT
FIRST SQUISHY BLOB OF FLESH...

10:42.062 --> 10:45.225
BECAUSE THE FIRST CUT
IS WHAT SETS THE TONE.

10:45.225 --> 10:51.111
IT DETERMINES EVERY SINGLE MOVE
FROM THAT POINT ON.

10:51.111 --> 10:53.694
SO, YOU HAVE TO BE CAREFUL.

10:53.694 --> 10:55.115
YOU HAVE TO BE SURE.

10:55.115 --> 10:59.700
OR YOU'RE IN TROUBLE.

11:00.620 --> 11:02.993
Dr. Herman: IT'S LIKE A...
Arizona: [ LAUGHS ]

11:02.993 --> 11:04.544
JUST LOOK AT THEM.

11:04.544 --> 11:07.047
Alex: WHO?
ARIZONA AND HERMAN -- THEY'RE
PRACTICALLY JOINED AT THE HIP.

11:07.047 --> 11:08.548
Arizona: I'LL TAKE
ONE OF THOSE, TOO.

11:08.548 --> 11:09.920
WELL, SHE IS
HERMAN'S FELLOW.

11:09.920 --> 11:11.631
ISN'T SHE SORT OF SUPPOSED
TO FOLLOW HERMAN AROUND?

11:11.631 --> 11:14.004
THEY'RE LAUGHING
ALL THE TIME,
[ NICOLE AND ARIZONA LAUGHING ]

11:14.004 --> 11:17.057
AND ARIZONA
SEEMS SO...

11:17.057 --> 11:18.678
HAPPY --
LIKE REALLY HAPPY.

11:18.678 --> 11:19.429
SO?

11:19.429 --> 11:21.511
YOU SEEM HAPPY...ISH.

11:21.511 --> 11:23.683
WHAT DO YOU EVEN CARE?
I DON'T, OBVIOUSLY.

11:23.683 --> 11:26.146
I'M JUST
MAKING CONVERSATION.

11:26.146 --> 11:28.358
Arizona: [ LAUGHS ]

11:28.358 --> 11:31.311
DON'T YOU GUYS THINK IT'S WEIRD
HOW THEY'RE ALWAYS TOGETHER?
THEY'RE NOT
ALWAYS TOGETHER.

11:31.311 --> 11:33.073
THEY DO BUNK UP TOGETHER
SOMETIMES.

11:33.073 --> 11:34.614
WHAT?
ALEX.
ROBBINS HAS BEEN CRASHING
WITH HERMAN.

11:34.614 --> 11:36.076
SHE HASN'T SLEPT
AT THE HOUSE ALL WEEK.

11:36.076 --> 11:37.027
WHAT?!
ALEX.

11:37.027 --> 11:38.448
I-I DON'T MEAN
LIKE THAT.

11:38.448 --> 11:40.120
THEY'RE NOT TOGETHER TOGETHER,
AND YOU KNOW THAT.

11:40.120 --> 11:41.241
[ Sarcastically ]
MM-HMM.

11:41.241 --> 11:43.243
ARIZONA USED TO HATE HER.
NOW THEY'RE HAVING SLEEPOVERS?

11:43.243 --> 11:46.036
WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING, RIGHT,
THAT THEY'RE GETTING ALONG?

11:46.036 --> 11:47.918
HERMAN'S NOT EXACTLY
THE WARMEST PERSON, SO --

11:47.918 --> 11:48.879
YEAH, WHATEVER.

11:48.879 --> 11:50.250
WHEN YOU
TALK TO DEREK TONIGHT,

11:50.250 --> 11:52.332
WOULD YOU ASK HIM SOMETHING FOR
ME WITHOUT SAYING IT'S FOR ME?

11:52.332 --> 11:53.673
I DON'T KNOW THAT I W--

11:53.673 --> 11:55.095
JUST ASK HIM
WHAT HE'D USE

11:55.095 --> 11:57.097
TO AVOID DISRUPTING
THE GRATIOLET RADIATIONS

11:57.097 --> 11:58.929
OFF THE GENICULATE BODY
OF THE THALAMUS.

11:58.929 --> 12:00.640
WHY DON'T YOU
ASK HIM THAT?
NO, NO, NO.

12:00.640 --> 12:02.182
NO, NO. THAT'S THE POINT.
YOU ASK HIM.

12:02.182 --> 12:03.513
I CAN'T
ASK HIM FOR HELP.

12:03.513 --> 12:05.976
I CANNOT LISTEN
TO THE SMUGNESS IN HIS VOICE.

12:05.976 --> 12:07.187
YOU CAN HEAR IT.

12:07.187 --> 12:09.399
HE HAS TRANSCONTINENTAL
SMUGNESS. YOU KNOW WHAT?

12:09.399 --> 12:11.521
FORGET IT. I'M FINE.
I DON'T NEED HIM.

12:11.521 --> 12:12.562
I DON'T NEED DEREK.

12:12.562 --> 12:14.154
I WILL
FIGURE IT OUT MYSELF.

12:14.154 --> 12:15.816
WHEN DID THIS HAPPEN?

12:15.816 --> 12:17.117
SHE FOUND
THE PERFECT REBOUND

12:17.117 --> 12:19.780
WITHOUT HAVING TO ACTUALLY
FIND A [Laughing] REBOUND --

12:19.780 --> 12:22.032
I MEAN, SHE JUST GETS
ALL THE GOOD TIMES AND THE FUN,

12:22.032 --> 12:24.034
NONE OF THE BAD TIMES
OR THE MESS,

12:24.034 --> 12:25.575
NO CHANCE OF GETTING HURT.

12:25.575 --> 12:27.918
YOU DON'T EVEN HAVE TO WAX.
IT'S NOT FAIR!

12:27.918 --> 12:29.169
[ SLURPS ]

12:29.169 --> 12:31.501
OH, MY GOD. AM I
SERIOUSLY WISHING FOR
A SEXLESS RELATIONSHIP

12:31.501 --> 12:32.923
WHERE I DON'T
HAVE TO GROOM MYSELF?

12:32.923 --> 12:33.924
IS THAT WHERE I AM NOW?

12:33.924 --> 12:35.215
IT SOUNDS GOOD TO ME.

12:35.215 --> 12:36.296
WELCOME TO MY LIFE
THESE DAYS.

12:36.296 --> 12:37.757
YOU CHICKS
NEED TO GET LAID.

12:37.757 --> 12:39.139
THAT ALSO
SOUNDS GOOD TO ME.

12:39.139 --> 12:41.181
[ SIGHS ]
NOT WITHOUT
THE GROOMING.

12:41.181 --> 12:42.803
IT'S IN THERE.
HE CAN FIND IT.

12:42.803 --> 12:44.224
WHAT, HE CAN'T DO
A LITTLE WORK FIRST?

12:44.224 --> 12:46.146
[ CHUCKLES ]
I LIKE HER.

12:46.146 --> 12:47.187
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:47.187 --> 12:48.728
[ CASH REGISTER BEEPING ]

12:51.151 --> 12:52.652
Miranda: EDDIE.

12:52.652 --> 12:54.104
Arizona: EXCUSE ME?

12:54.104 --> 12:55.275
UH, GLENDA CASTILLO,

12:55.275 --> 12:57.197
THE PATIENT YOU AND HERMAN
TURNED DOWN LAST WEEK,

12:57.197 --> 12:59.109
HER HUSBAND'S NAME
WAS EDDIE.

12:59.109 --> 13:01.491
I LOST HIM
SIX MONTHS AGO

13:01.491 --> 13:04.574
AFTER HE WAS INJURED
IN A HEAD-ON COLLISION.

13:04.574 --> 13:06.576
MY HANDS
WERE INSIDE OF HIS BODY

13:06.576 --> 13:07.998
WHEN HIS HEART
STOPPED BEATING.

13:07.998 --> 13:09.499
MY HANDS HELD GLENDA'S

13:09.499 --> 13:12.002
WHEN I TOLD HER
EDDIE DIED ON MY WATCH.

13:12.002 --> 13:14.504
THREE WEEKS LATER,
SHE FOUND OUT SHE WAS PREGNANT.

13:14.504 --> 13:16.006
SHE'S NOT INSURED,

13:16.006 --> 13:18.218
BUT SHE REMEMBERED ME
AND THIS HOSPITAL,

13:18.218 --> 13:19.179
SO, SHE CAME HERE

13:19.179 --> 13:21.221
TO SEE IF I COULD GIVE HER
SOME PRENATAL CARE,

13:21.221 --> 13:23.183
AND GUESS
WHAT WE FOUND OUT.

13:23.183 --> 13:25.926
HER BABY HAS A TUMOR --

13:25.926 --> 13:29.599
A LARGE, DANGEROUS TUMOR

13:29.599 --> 13:32.062
THAT'S NOT JUST MESSING
WITH THE BABY'S SYSTEM,

13:32.062 --> 13:33.523
IT'S MESSING WITH HERS.

13:33.523 --> 13:35.645
[ SIGHS ] I COULDN'T SAVE
HER HUSBAND'S LIFE,

13:35.645 --> 13:37.697
BUT I CAN HELP
SAVE HER BABY.

13:37.697 --> 13:39.699
I-I OWE THIS
WOMAN THAT MUCH.

13:39.699 --> 13:43.073
HERMAN HAS TO
TAKE HER ON AS A PATIENT.

13:43.073 --> 13:44.614
JUST -- JUST HAVE HER
MEET GLENDA, ALL RIGHT?

13:44.614 --> 13:46.206
THEN SHE'LL --
I CAN'T, I CAN'T!

13:46.206 --> 13:48.368
I CAN'T TRICK HER INTO
SEEING A PATIENT SHE
DOESN'T WANT TO TREAT.

13:48.368 --> 13:49.449
WHO'S IN CHARGE
OF HER SCHEDULE?

13:49.449 --> 13:51.211
WHO TELLS HER
WHERE TO GO AND WHEN?

13:51.211 --> 13:55.455
WHO TELLS HER WHAT SURGERY
OR POST-OP OR ANONYMOUS CONSULT

13:55.455 --> 13:58.218
SHE SHOULD SEE NEXT?
[ SIGHS ]

13:58.218 --> 13:59.299
UH...

13:59.299 --> 14:00.380
[ HEARTBEAT ]

14:00.380 --> 14:02.262
I'M CONCERNED
ABOUT HER BLOOD PRESSURE.

14:02.262 --> 14:05.175
IT'S INCREASED TO 140 SYSTOLIC
IN THE PAST WEEK,

14:05.175 --> 14:06.887
AND HER SWELLING'S
GOTTEN WORSE.

14:06.887 --> 14:08.098
Glenda:
UH, I USED TO HAVE ANKLES.

14:08.098 --> 14:10.100
NOW I HAVE
BALLOONS WITH TOES.

14:10.100 --> 14:11.471
[ LAUGHTER ]

14:11.471 --> 14:15.185
SO, YOUR BABY HAS A LARGE TUMOR
IN HIS LOWER BACK.

14:15.185 --> 14:16.186
IT'S MOST LIKELY BENIGN,

14:16.186 --> 14:18.738
BUT BECAUSE OF ITS SIZE
AND VASCULAR NATURE,

14:18.738 --> 14:21.441
IT COULD CAUSE AN ACCUMULATION
OF FLUIDS IN THE BABY.

14:21.441 --> 14:23.904
[ SIGHS ] BUT THE TUMOR
CAN BE REMOVED, RIGHT?

14:24.945 --> 14:27.287
DR. BAILEY
SAYS AMAZING THINGS ABOUT YOU,

14:27.287 --> 14:29.079
THAT YOU'RE
ONE OF THE BEST.

14:29.079 --> 14:31.081
BAILEY SAID THAT?

14:31.081 --> 14:32.702
HOW FLATTERING.

14:32.702 --> 14:34.044
THAT WAS
GLENDA CASTILLO.

14:34.044 --> 14:36.917
I TOLD YOU NO
TWICE NOW.

14:36.917 --> 14:39.709
AND YOU, HOW AM I
SUPPOSED TO TRUST YOU AT ALL

14:39.709 --> 14:41.091
WHEN YOU
PULL SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

14:41.091 --> 14:42.002
SHE DIDN'T DO ANYTHING

14:42.002 --> 14:43.763
EXCEPT TRY TO GET
YOUR HELP ON A PATIENT

14:43.763 --> 14:45.425
WHO NEEDS YOUR HELP.

14:45.425 --> 14:47.887
BUT IF YOU HEARD HER STORY,
IF YOU KNEW SHE WAS --

14:47.887 --> 14:49.719
IS THAT HOW
BAILEY CONVINCED YOU?

14:49.719 --> 14:51.641
IT'S A TACTIC, ROBBINS,

14:51.641 --> 14:54.564
APPEALING TO YOUR
SAD, BLEEDING HEART.

14:54.564 --> 14:56.106
DOESN'T WORK WITH ME.

14:56.106 --> 14:57.477
WELL, THEN, LET ME
APPEAL TO YOUR EGO.

14:57.477 --> 14:59.359
YOU WALK AROUND HERE
TELLING ANYONE WHO WILL LISTEN

14:59.359 --> 15:00.780
THAT YOU'RE THE BEST.

15:00.780 --> 15:02.782
WELL, THEN,
BE THE BEST.

15:02.782 --> 15:05.155
YOU CAN SAVE
HER BABY'S LIFE,

15:05.155 --> 15:07.157
SO SAVE
THAT BABY'S LIFE!

15:09.739 --> 15:11.411
NO.

15:11.411 --> 15:12.332
OHH.

15:16.456 --> 15:18.088
WHAT THE HELL?
ROBBINS, DROP IT.

15:18.088 --> 15:20.300
NO, I GET THAT -- I GET
THAT I'VE SEEN TUMORS
LIKE THAT BEFORE,

15:20.300 --> 15:21.711
BUT THIS CAN'T ALL BE
ABOUT MY EDUCATION.

15:21.711 --> 15:23.173
I MEAN, AT SOME POINT,
I HAVE TO --

15:23.173 --> 15:25.755
AT SOME POINT, WE
HAVE TO MAKE DECISIONS
AND STICK TO THEM.

15:25.755 --> 15:28.008
I WISH WE HAD TIME,
BUT WE DON'T.

15:28.008 --> 15:30.180
WE HAVE VERY LITTLE CONTROL
OVER THE TIME WE HAVE,

15:30.180 --> 15:31.391
AND WE HAVE A PLAN.

15:31.391 --> 15:33.223
CAN'T WE
MAKE AN EXCEPTION?

15:33.223 --> 15:34.854
CAN'T WE JUST, YOU KNOW,
SORT OF ADJUST THE PLAN?

15:34.854 --> 15:36.977
YOU -- FINE.
YOU WANT TO?

15:36.977 --> 15:38.818
ADJUST THE PLAN.

15:38.818 --> 15:40.520
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

15:40.520 --> 15:41.901
TAKE DOWN
ONE OF THESE CARDS

15:41.901 --> 15:42.983
SO WE HAVE TIME
TO HELP MRS. CASTILLO.

15:42.983 --> 15:44.524
WHICH ONE?

15:44.524 --> 15:47.327
HOW ABOUT MEGHAN CARLSON --
CONGENITAL AIRWAY OBSTRUCTION?

15:47.327 --> 15:48.658
HER HUSBAND'S
IN IRAQ RIGHT NOW.

15:48.658 --> 15:51.161
OR JULIE HALL --
VASA PREVIA.

15:51.161 --> 15:53.373
SHE WENT THROUGH TWO YEARS
OF FERTILITY TREATMENTS.

15:53.373 --> 15:55.205
SO, PICK ONE.

15:55.205 --> 15:57.077
DECIDE WHICH BABY
DOESN'T GET TO LIVE

15:57.077 --> 15:59.169
SO GLENDA CASTILLO'S
DOES.

15:59.169 --> 16:00.210
GO AHEAD.

16:00.210 --> 16:02.882
PICK A CARD.
YOU CHOOSE.

16:07.297 --> 16:09.179
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

16:27.867 --> 16:29.659
[ MONITOR BEEPS,
MACHINERY WHIRRING ]

16:29.659 --> 16:31.451
Dr. Herman:
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

16:33.953 --> 16:35.325
NO.

16:35.325 --> 16:37.457
NO.

16:37.457 --> 16:39.079
GET ME OUT!

16:39.079 --> 16:41.501
GET ME OUT OF HERE!

16:41.501 --> 16:42.542
GET ME OUT!

16:42.542 --> 16:44.003
YOU HAVE TO.
I DON'T.

16:44.003 --> 16:46.005
THE RADIATION TREATMENTS
ARE GOING TO HELP.

16:46.005 --> 16:47.967
THEY ARE GONNA SHRINK
THE BORDERS OF THE TUMOR,

16:47.967 --> 16:49.429
WHICH WILL
MAKE IT EASIER TO RESECT.

16:49.429 --> 16:50.970
IT'S A MINIMAL GAIN
FOR YOU.

16:50.970 --> 16:53.683
I WILL TAKE WHAT I CAN GET.
I AM TRYING TO SAVE YOUR LIFE!

16:53.683 --> 16:56.226
YOU ARE MAKING ME FEEL
LIKE I'VE ALREADY DIED.

16:56.226 --> 16:58.017
I'M SICK.
I'M LOSING MY HAIR.

16:58.017 --> 17:00.600
I REFUSE TO SPEND
THE LAST FEW MONTHS OF MY LIFE

17:00.600 --> 17:02.102
FEELING LIKE
A PILE OF CRAP.

17:02.102 --> 17:03.103
NO MORE.

17:03.103 --> 17:04.814
THAT'S FINAL.

17:04.814 --> 17:07.197
Woman over P.A:
DR. STANLEY, PLEASE REPORT...

17:07.197 --> 17:10.029
I AM GOING TO GIVE YOU
MORE THAN A FEW MONTHS.

17:10.029 --> 17:12.822
I AM GOING
TO SAVE YOUR LIFE.

17:12.822 --> 17:15.155
AND I AM ABOUT TO GET UP
IN FRONT OF A BUNCH OF PEOPLE

17:15.155 --> 17:17.287
AND TELL THEM
HOW I PLAN ON DOING IT.

17:17.287 --> 17:20.210
IT MAKES IT REALLY HARD
FOR ME TO DO THAT

17:20.210 --> 17:21.961
OR EVEN CARE
ABOUT DOING THAT

17:21.961 --> 17:23.833
WHEN YOU DON'T
SEEM TO CARE AT ALL!

17:23.833 --> 17:26.166
WELL,
THAT'S YOUR PROBLEM.

17:26.166 --> 17:27.547
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

17:27.547 --> 17:30.170
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

17:31.171 --> 17:33.513
Richard:
WELL, THE WORD'S SPREADING.

17:33.513 --> 17:35.095
THIS WAS
A GOOD IDEA, HUNT --

17:35.095 --> 17:37.637
A MASTER CLASS
IN NEUROSURGERY.

17:37.637 --> 17:39.599
THIS IS GONNA PUT
AMELIA SHEPHERD ON THE MAP.

17:39.599 --> 17:41.020
MM. UNLESS IT FAILS.

17:41.020 --> 17:42.312
IT WON'T.

17:42.312 --> 17:45.064
IF IT DOES...

17:45.064 --> 17:47.567
THERE'S A LESSON
IN THAT, TOO.

17:50.950 --> 17:53.032
SO, SHE JUST SPITBALLS
THIS STUFF WITH YOU?

17:53.032 --> 17:56.035
IT'S JUST THE TWO OF YOU
HANGING OUT, TALKING TUMOR?

17:56.035 --> 17:57.036
PRETTY MUCH.

17:57.036 --> 17:59.038
I WANT TO TALK TUMOR!
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:59.038 --> 18:02.041
I WANT TO TALK TUMOR
SO BAD.
SHH!

18:02.041 --> 18:04.504
OH, MY GOD.
LOOK AT THAT THING
YEAH.

18:04.504 --> 18:06.206
PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS

18:06.206 --> 18:08.208
TO TREAT DR. HERMAN'S TUMOR
WITH RADIATION

18:08.208 --> 18:10.130
PROVED UNSUCCESSFUL.

18:10.130 --> 18:13.173
I HAD HOPED TO USE
HIGH RADIOACTIVE DOSES

18:13.173 --> 18:14.844
TO REDUCE THE MARGINS,

18:14.844 --> 18:16.516
BUT AT THIS JUNCTURE,

18:16.516 --> 18:19.599
THAT COURSE
SEEMS TO BE UNREALISTIC.

18:21.221 --> 18:23.102
BUT THAT'S NOT ENOUGH
TO MAKE ME QUIT.

18:23.102 --> 18:29.068
THIS TUMOR IS FIERCE
AND INTIMIDATING AND AGGRESSIVE,

18:29.068 --> 18:30.190
BUT SO AM I.

18:32.782 --> 18:34.694
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

18:34.694 --> 18:35.995
Dr. Herman:
NOW, THE TRICK TO THIS IS,

18:35.995 --> 18:38.368
YOU CAN'T TOUCH THE VESSEL WHILE
YOU'RE LASERING THE MASS --

18:38.368 --> 18:39.239
NOT EVEN A LITTLE BIT.

18:39.239 --> 18:40.620
IF YOU DO...

18:40.620 --> 18:42.622
Arizona: THE FIELD FILLS WITH
BLOOD, OBSCURING THE CAMERA,

18:42.622 --> 18:44.334
AND VISUALIZATION
IS COMPROMISED.

18:44.334 --> 18:47.587
FIRST, I NEED TO SEE THE TUMOR,
ALL OF IT --

18:47.587 --> 18:50.460
EVERY MARGIN,
EVERY LAST RIPPLE AND RIDGE.

18:50.460 --> 18:52.422
SO, WHAT DO YOU DO?

18:52.422 --> 18:53.593
I HAVE TWO CHOICES --

18:53.593 --> 18:55.845
OPEN HER UP
AND STOP THE BLEEDING IF I CAN,

18:55.845 --> 18:58.388
OR DELIVER THE BABY
REGARDLESS OF HOW EARLY.

18:58.388 --> 18:59.469
VERY GOOD.

18:59.469 --> 19:02.061
SO, I WILL EMPLOY
FLUORESCEIN DYE

19:02.061 --> 19:04.354
TO DELINEATE
EVERY BORDER OF THE TUMOR,

19:04.354 --> 19:07.527
TO HELP ME ANTICIPATE
EVERY POSSIBLE PROBLEM

19:07.527 --> 19:09.028
BEFORE I GET TO IT.

19:09.028 --> 19:10.940
I DON'T WANT TO LEAVE ANYTHING
UP TO CHANCE.

19:10.940 --> 19:12.362
Julie: [ GROANING ]
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

19:12.362 --> 19:14.073
Dr. Herman:
WHAT HAPPENED?

19:14.073 --> 19:15.275
Maggie:
THE PRESSURE'S DROPPED.

19:15.275 --> 19:16.776
SHE'S IN A LOT OF PAIN,
AND SHE'S CRAMPING.

19:16.776 --> 19:18.037
Julie: IT HURTS!
IT HURTS, IT HURTS!

19:18.037 --> 19:20.079
Arizona: IT'S OKAY, JULIE.
WE'VE GOT YOU, WE'VE GOT YOU.

19:20.079 --> 19:21.160
SHE HAS A VASA PREVIA.

19:21.160 --> 19:22.662
SHE'S SCHEDULED
FOR AN ABLATION TOMORROW.

19:22.662 --> 19:24.914
I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO GET HER PRESSURE BACK UP,

19:24.914 --> 19:26.546
BUT THERE IS NO
FETAL HEARTBEAT.

19:26.546 --> 19:28.047
[ FLATLINE ]

19:28.047 --> 19:30.089
DAMN IT.
WHERE'S HER HUSBAND?

19:31.551 --> 19:33.092
Julie: IS THAT BLOOD?!
I'M BLEEDING?!

19:33.092 --> 19:35.094
GOWN ME.
KEEP HIM OUT OF HERE.

19:35.094 --> 19:37.797
ROBBINS, YOU'RE GONNA GET THIS
BABY OUT RIGHT HERE, RIGHT NOW.

19:37.797 --> 19:38.888
HERE?

19:38.888 --> 19:40.600
WE NEED A C-SECTION TRAY
SET UP IN HERE.

19:40.600 --> 19:41.891
CALL PEDS.
GET AN INCUBATOR, STAT.

19:41.891 --> 19:43.353
WAIT! WHAT?!
I'M GONNA HAVE THE BABY NOW?!

19:43.353 --> 19:45.805
JULIE, I'M GONNA
GIVE YOU SOMETHING TO
CALM YOU DOWN, OKAY?

19:45.805 --> 19:47.767
I NEVER HAD TO DO A CRASH "C"
ON MY OWN BEFORE, OKAY?

19:47.767 --> 19:49.309
I MEAN,
N-NOT LIKE THIS.
Dr. Herman:
YOU KNOW WHAT TO DO.

19:49.309 --> 19:52.151
IT'S THE SAME THREE BASIC STEPS,
JUST LIKE ANY OTHER C-SECTION --

19:52.151 --> 19:53.983
OPEN THE ABDOMEN,
OPEN THE UTERUS, DELIVER.

19:53.983 --> 19:55.024
OKAY, I'M OKAY.

19:55.024 --> 19:56.776
PRESSURE'S STEADY
AT 100/60.

19:56.776 --> 19:58.318
OKAY, I-I CAN DO THIS.
BETADINE.

19:58.318 --> 19:59.078
OKAY.

20:00.490 --> 20:02.121
ROBBINS?
I'LL DO -- I'LL DO THIS.

20:02.121 --> 20:03.202
IT'S FINE, ROBBINS.

20:03.202 --> 20:04.284
I'LL DO IT.

20:04.284 --> 20:05.495
SCALPEL.

20:09.379 --> 20:10.710
[ SOBBING ]

20:10.710 --> 20:12.131
[ Muffled ]
I'M SO SORRY.

20:12.131 --> 20:14.884
WE DID EVERYTHING
WE COULD DO.

20:14.884 --> 20:16.756
[ SOBBING CONTINUES ]

20:16.756 --> 20:19.008
I'M SO SORRY.

20:28.147 --> 20:31.020
GOOD JOB. LET'S GO.

20:32.692 --> 20:35.525
[ CRYING, SNIFFLING ]

20:35.525 --> 20:37.116
STOP CRYING.

20:37.116 --> 20:38.948
OH, FOR THE LOVE OF --

20:38.948 --> 20:40.069
STOP CRYING!
I'M --

20:40.069 --> 20:41.621
STOP IT NOW! JUST...

20:42.912 --> 20:44.624
STOP IT RIGHT NOW.

20:48.998 --> 20:51.170
THERE'S NO TIME
FOR CRYING.

20:51.170 --> 20:52.542
[ MARKER SCRATCHING ]

20:52.542 --> 20:53.873
WE HAVE WORK TO DO.

20:58.298 --> 20:59.509
WHAT?

20:59.509 --> 21:01.591
H-HOW CAN YOU EVEN --

21:01.591 --> 21:03.092
'CAUSE THAT'S THE WAY IT GOES,
ROBBINS.

21:04.344 --> 21:05.305
[ SIGHS ]

21:05.305 --> 21:07.056
CALL BAILEY.

21:07.056 --> 21:08.147
TELL HER WE'RE ON.

21:25.535 --> 21:27.667
[ MACHINERY WHIRRING ]

21:27.667 --> 21:30.960
Amelia: NOW, ARGUABLY, THE MOST
IMPORTANT PART OF THE BRAIN

21:30.960 --> 21:34.043
IS THE PART
THAT MAKES US HOPE...

21:34.043 --> 21:36.586
DREAM...

21:36.586 --> 21:38.217
IMAGINE.

21:38.217 --> 21:41.130
ONE SINGULAR,
ALMOST IMMEASURABLE PART

21:41.130 --> 21:45.555
IS WHAT MAKES YOU YOU...

21:45.555 --> 21:47.727
AND ME ME...

21:47.727 --> 21:50.019
AND EVERYONE...EVERYONE.

21:50.019 --> 21:53.142
IT'S TECHNICALLY CALLED
THE FORNIX,

21:53.142 --> 21:57.857
BUT I CALL IT
THE "DREAM BOX."

21:57.857 --> 22:00.740
THE QUESTION IS...
[ MONITOR BEEPS ]

22:00.740 --> 22:04.113
...WHAT HAPPENS WHEN
THE DREAM BOX IS BEING INVADED,

22:04.113 --> 22:08.077
WHEN A TUMOR IS SO LARGE,
SO DEMANDING,

22:08.077 --> 22:11.210
IT'S SUCKING
THE DREAM BOX DRY?

22:11.210 --> 22:12.211
IT'S TAKING OVER --

22:12.211 --> 22:17.006
IT'S STEALING AWAY
HOPES AND DREAMS.

22:17.006 --> 22:20.339
IMAGINE,
WHEN THAT TUMOR IS REMOVED,

22:20.339 --> 22:24.133
WHAT -- WHAT
WILL ACTUALLY BE LEFT?

22:24.133 --> 22:28.347
OR, RATHER, WHO IS LEFT?

22:28.347 --> 22:31.060
ANYTHING?

22:31.060 --> 22:33.733
ANYONE?

22:33.733 --> 22:35.274
Dr. Herman: I REMEMBER MY MOM
TELLING ME ONCE

22:35.274 --> 22:38.107
THAT WHEN WE DIE,
WE GO TO HEAVEN.

22:38.107 --> 22:40.029
I COULDN'T PICTURE IT.

22:40.029 --> 22:43.282
ALL I COULD IMAGINE
WAS WHAT WE SEE IN CARTOONS --

22:43.282 --> 22:47.196
LITTLE PEOPLE IN ROBES
WITH WINGS, SITTING ON CLOUDS.

22:47.196 --> 22:49.288
BUT NOBODY REALLY KNOWS
WHAT'S UP THERE, DO THEY?

22:49.288 --> 22:50.540
Arizona:
WHEN I WAS A KID,

22:50.540 --> 22:52.832
I USED TO THINK
THAT WE WERE LIKE DANDELIONS --

22:52.832 --> 22:56.756
LIKE, THE PART THAT MAKES US US
WOULD JUST BLOW AWAY

22:56.756 --> 22:58.628
AND LAND
AND GROW INTO --

22:58.628 --> 23:00.089
I DON'T WANT
TO BE BURIED, BY THE WAY.

23:00.089 --> 23:01.421
HAVE ME CREMATED.

23:01.421 --> 23:03.052
W-- EXCUSE ME?

23:03.052 --> 23:05.004
IF I SURVIVE THE SURGERY
BUT DON'T WAKE UP,

23:05.004 --> 23:07.807
GIVE ME FIVE DAYS --
A WEEK, TOPS --

23:07.807 --> 23:09.138
THEN PULL THE PLUG.
THIS IS --

23:09.138 --> 23:10.600
WE DON'T NEED
TO BE TALKING ABOUT THIS.

23:10.600 --> 23:13.222
IF I DO WAKE UP BUT I'M
DEPENDENT ON VENTS OR TUBES,

23:13.222 --> 23:14.564
PULL THE PLUG THEN, TOO.

23:14.564 --> 23:16.816
Y-YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU'RE NOT -- YOU'RE NOT DYING.

23:16.816 --> 23:18.357
YOU'RE NOT
GONNA WAKE UP GORKED.

23:18.357 --> 23:20.570
SHEPHERD KNOWS
WHAT SHE'S DOING. SHE DOES.
OKAY. SURE.

23:20.570 --> 23:22.191
SHE DOES!
I HEARD YOU.

23:24.113 --> 23:25.284
[ SIGHS ]
[ WINGS FLUTTERING ]

23:25.284 --> 23:27.076
THAT BIRD
IS GONNA POOP ON US.

23:27.076 --> 23:28.197
OH...

23:28.197 --> 23:29.489
WHAT'S NEXT TODAY?

23:29.489 --> 23:30.740
GLENDA CASTILLO.

23:30.740 --> 23:32.121
Glenda: I'M SO GLAD
YOU BROUGHT ME BACK IN.

23:32.121 --> 23:35.084
[ HEARTBEAT ]
HAVE A LOOK.

23:35.084 --> 23:36.335
WELL, THE TERATOMA
HAS GROWN.

23:36.335 --> 23:39.709
IT'S SHOWING
EARLY SIGNS OF HYDROPS.

23:39.709 --> 23:42.752
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?
GLENDA, YOUR BABY'S
RETAINING FLUID,

23:42.752 --> 23:45.044
WHICH IS STARTING
TO AFFECT HIS HEART.

23:45.044 --> 23:47.176
I'M RECOMMENDING
WE DO THE SURGERY TONIGHT.

23:47.176 --> 23:48.007
TONIGHT?

23:48.007 --> 23:49.759
NO, THAT'S
WAY TOO SOON.

23:49.759 --> 23:52.051
THE TUMOR IS CREATING PRESSURE
ON YOUR PLACENTA.

23:52.051 --> 23:54.223
IT'S NOT ONLY
ENDANGERING THE BABY,

23:54.223 --> 23:55.815
BUT NOW IT'S
PUTTING YOU AT RISK.

23:55.815 --> 23:58.017
BUT MY BABY
WOULDN'T SURVIVE, WOULD HE,

23:58.017 --> 24:00.269
IF YOU SUDDENLY
HAD TO DELIVER?

24:00.269 --> 24:01.981
'CAUSE I'M ONLY
24 WEEKS ALONG,

24:01.981 --> 24:03.983
AND I-I KNOW THAT IT
WOULD HELP HIM IF HE HAD
TIME TO GROW, RIGHT?

24:03.983 --> 24:05.865
IF I COULD JUST HOLD ON
FOR A FEW MORE WEEKS...

24:05.865 --> 24:07.156
IT'S NOT
WHAT'S BEST FOR YOU.

24:07.156 --> 24:08.698
I DON'T CARE ABOUT ME.

24:08.698 --> 24:10.620
GLENDA, IF DR. HERMAN
THINKS THAT --

24:10.620 --> 24:13.202
NO, MY HUSBAND IS DEAD.

24:13.202 --> 24:15.705
[ Voice breaking ] BUT THIS BABY
THAT IS INSIDE OF ME,

24:15.705 --> 24:18.037
THIS BABY OF OURS,
I CANNOT RISK HIS LIFE.

24:18.037 --> 24:19.579
I WON'T.

24:19.579 --> 24:21.080
SO, IF THERE IS A CHOICE

24:21.080 --> 24:23.843
BETWEEN HELPING ME
OR HELPING MY BABY,

24:23.843 --> 24:25.174
I CHOOSE MY BABY.

24:26.966 --> 24:29.218
WHAT DOES SHE THINK
WE'RE TRYING TO DO HERE?

24:29.218 --> 24:31.010
I AM NOT NEGOTIATING
WITH A PATIENT.

24:31.010 --> 24:33.803
I AM THE DOCTOR. I'M GONNA
TELL HER WHEN WE'RE GO --
[ LAUGHS ]

24:35.474 --> 24:37.056
I'M SORRY.

24:37.056 --> 24:38.518
ROBBINS,
WHAT'S THE HELL?
WHAT'S FUNNY
ABOUT THIS?

24:38.518 --> 24:40.690
I'M SORRY, I'M SORRY.
IT'S JUST -- IT'S JUST --

24:40.690 --> 24:43.523
IT'S FUNNY LISTENING
TO YOU GET SO BENT OUT OF SHAPE

24:43.523 --> 24:44.984
WHEN THIS IS
THE EXACT SAME THING

24:44.984 --> 24:46.526
THAT YOU'VE BEEN DOING
TO AMELIA SHEPHERD

24:46.526 --> 24:48.027
EVER SINCE SHE OFFERED
TO SAVE HER LIFE.

24:48.027 --> 24:49.869
I MEAN, SHE HAS.
EXACTLY.

24:49.869 --> 24:52.071
"WE'LL DO THE SURGERY
WHEN I'M READY."

24:52.071 --> 24:53.112
AND IT'S SO FRUSTRATING.

24:53.112 --> 24:55.114
IT'S TORTURE,
AND IT DRIVES US CRAZY.

24:55.114 --> 24:56.996
SO, IT'S JUST FUN
TO WATCH IT HAPPEN TO YOU.

24:56.996 --> 24:58.077
IT'S LIKE
DIVINE JUSTICE.

24:58.077 --> 24:59.378
PRETEND
THAT I'M NOT HERE.

24:59.378 --> 25:01.380
KEEP GOING.

25:03.462 --> 25:06.215
I WILL GIVE MS. CASTILLO
AN EXTRA WEEK,

25:06.215 --> 25:08.087
BUT I WANT HER
ADMITTED.

25:08.087 --> 25:09.969
AND IF SHE SO MUCH AS
HICCUPS FUNNY,

25:09.969 --> 25:11.090
I'M TAKING HER
TO SURGERY.

25:11.090 --> 25:12.341
J-- UNDERSTOOD.

25:13.262 --> 25:15.935
HEY, THANK YOU
FOR TAKING HER CASE.

25:17.687 --> 25:18.938
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:18.938 --> 25:20.139
OH, SHUT UP.

25:20.139 --> 25:21.691
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:21.691 --> 25:24.734
[ LAUGHTER ]
[ LIQUID POURS ]

25:24.734 --> 25:27.066
♪ I WANT TO TELL YOU
EVERYTHING ♪

25:27.066 --> 25:28.818
[ Laughing ]
I CAN'T...

25:29.989 --> 25:34.363
♪ MY DARKEST SECRETS,
WON'T YOU KEEP? ♪
HOLY -- OH. AH. AH.

25:34.363 --> 25:39.579
HOW DO I ACCESS THAT AREA OF
THE BRAIN WHEN IT'S SO HIDDEN?

25:39.579 --> 25:42.331
AND ONCE I ACCESS THAT AREA,

25:42.331 --> 25:46.005
EVEN WITH THE PERFECT TOOLS,
THE PERFECT APPROACH...

25:46.005 --> 25:50.970
♪ I'LL SHARE
MY HOUSE AND THINGS WITH YOU ♪
...HOW DO I KEEP
FROM SCREWING IT UP?

25:50.970 --> 25:55.174
♪ THIS WORLD OF MINE
IS YOUR WORLD, TOO ♪
AMELIA: If there's
edema, it's post-fixed.

25:55.174 --> 25:56.806
It's too narrow,
too close the fornix.

25:56.806 --> 25:59.058
If I hit the hypothalamus,
game over.

25:59.058 --> 26:01.731
Not gonna work,
not gonna work, not gonna work.

26:01.731 --> 26:04.023
♪ LET IT GROW AROUND ♪
COME ON!

26:04.023 --> 26:05.314
DO YOU WANT SOME FOOD?

26:05.314 --> 26:06.986
Amelia: HAVE I
FIGURED THIS OUT YET?

26:06.986 --> 26:08.397
NO.

26:08.397 --> 26:12.151
THEN I DON'T WANT ANY FOOD.
♪ MY FEE-E-E-E-T ♪

26:12.151 --> 26:14.614
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

26:14.614 --> 26:16.746
♪ THEY'LL GROW AROUND ♪

26:16.746 --> 26:19.248
THIS HAS NEVER
BEEN DONE BEFORE.

26:19.248 --> 26:23.162
ALL THESE STEPS IN THIS ORDER
ON THIS KIND OF TUMOR

26:23.162 --> 26:25.004
HAS NEVER BEEN DONE.

26:25.004 --> 26:27.296
IS THAT A GOOD THING
OR A BAD THING?

26:27.296 --> 26:30.840
WHO DO I EVEN THINK I AM?
WHO AM I TO EVEN TRY THIS?

26:30.840 --> 26:32.051
OKAY, A BAD THING.

26:32.051 --> 26:33.172
[ SIGHS ]

26:35.635 --> 26:37.306
♪ AS THE DAYS
TURN INTO WEEKS ♪

26:37.306 --> 26:40.770
Stephanie:
HAVE YOU CALLED YOUR BROTHER?

26:40.770 --> 26:43.222
♪ WEEKS TO YEARS ♪
WHAT DID I SAY
ABOUT MY BROTHER?

26:43.222 --> 26:45.064
I KNOW.
YOU DON'T NEED HIM.

26:45.064 --> 26:47.687
I WAS JUST THINKING
YOU COULD,

26:47.687 --> 26:50.319
JUST TO HAVE SOMEONE
TO BOUNCE THESE IDEAS OFF OF

26:50.319 --> 26:53.993
WHO UNDERSTANDS THIS KIND OF
THING THE WAY THAT YOU DO --

26:53.993 --> 26:56.075
A PEER.

26:56.075 --> 26:57.997
HE MIGHT HAVE
A SUGGESTION.

26:57.997 --> 27:00.199
I DO NOT NEED
MY BROTHER!

27:00.199 --> 27:02.742
I AM NOT STUCK!
I AM THINKING!

27:02.742 --> 27:03.953
I AM FIGURING IT OUT!

27:03.953 --> 27:06.085
I AM RIGHT ON THE EDGE
OF FIGURING IT OUT,

27:06.085 --> 27:08.417
OF MAKING THE BREAKTHROUGH
OF A LIFETIME!

27:08.417 --> 27:09.548
I AM THIS CLOSE!

27:09.548 --> 27:11.751
MY GENIUS IS FLYING AROUND
THIS ROOM RIGHT NOW,

27:11.751 --> 27:14.013
TRYING TO FIND A CLEAR PATH
TO LAND ON ME,

27:14.013 --> 27:16.095
BUT I CAN'T CLEAR
THE RUNWAY FOR LANDING

27:16.095 --> 27:17.677
BECAUSE I CAN'T FIND
ANY QUIET

27:17.677 --> 27:21.180
BECAUSE SOME IDIOT RESIDENT
KEEPS TALKING TO ME!

27:23.723 --> 27:25.104
[ PAPERS RUSTLING ]

27:25.104 --> 27:28.477
♪ LET IT GROW AROUND ♪
I SHOULDN'T HAVE
SAID THAT.

27:28.477 --> 27:31.731
I DIDN'T MEAN IT.
I'M TIRED, AND I'M FRUSTRATED.

27:31.731 --> 27:33.773
I...

27:33.773 --> 27:35.775
I AM SO SORRY.
I JUST [SIGHS]

27:37.777 --> 27:39.989
THIS TUMOR
IS MAKING ME CRAZY.

27:39.989 --> 27:42.081
EDWARDS.

27:42.081 --> 27:44.453
AS BAD AS YOU WANT
TO GET THAT TUMOR,

27:44.453 --> 27:47.957
THAT'S AS BAD AS I WANT
TO WATCH YOU GET THAT TUMOR.

27:47.957 --> 27:52.001
YOU'RE TIRED AND FRUSTRATED
AND TERRIFIED, BUT GUESS WHAT.

27:52.001 --> 27:53.132
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN.

27:53.132 --> 27:55.755
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
MY MENTOR.

27:55.755 --> 27:58.177
YOU ARE MY MENTOR.

27:58.177 --> 28:03.222
I BELIEVE IN YOU,
I LOOK UP TO YOU,
I WANT TO BE YOU.

28:03.222 --> 28:05.224
THAT'S AN ENORMOUS
RESPONSIBILITY,

28:05.224 --> 28:07.146
SO DON'T CALL ME NAMES.

28:07.146 --> 28:11.690
AND STOP POUTING BECAUSE YOU
DON'T UNDERSTAND WHAT TO DO.

28:11.690 --> 28:16.155
BE WORTHY OF BEING BELIEVED IN,
OF BEING LOOKED UP TO.

28:16.155 --> 28:18.077
OR IF YOU CAN'T
ACTUALLY BE WORTHY,

28:18.077 --> 28:20.119
IF I AM ACTUALLY
WASTING MY TIME,

28:20.119 --> 28:22.992
IF THERE IS NOTHING ABOUT YOU
THAT IS SPECIAL OR WISE,

28:22.992 --> 28:24.163
FOR GOD'S SAKE,

28:24.163 --> 28:28.087
AT LEAST HAVE THE DECENCY
TO PRETEND THAT THERE IS.

28:28.087 --> 28:31.210
GET IT TOGETHER,
DR. SHEPHERD.

28:31.210 --> 28:36.465
♪ LET IT GROW AROUND ♪

28:36.465 --> 28:40.139
♪ MY FEE-E-E-E-T ♪

28:40.139 --> 28:42.051
[ SIGHS ]
♪ OOH ♪

28:42.051 --> 28:45.014
♪ LET IT GROW AROUND ♪

28:45.014 --> 28:48.978
GET IT TOGETHER,
DR. SHEPHERD.

28:48.978 --> 28:53.112
♪ MY FEE-E-E-E-T ♪

28:53.112 --> 28:55.694
Dr. Herman: [ LAUGHS ]
♪ OOH ♪

28:55.694 --> 28:57.196
♪ LET IT GROW AROUND ♪

28:57.196 --> 28:59.198
[ LAUGHS ]

28:59.198 --> 29:03.572
♪ MY FEE-E-E-E-T ♪

29:13.632 --> 29:15.504
[ CELLPHONE CHIMING,
VIBRATING ]

29:16.675 --> 29:18.377
[ LAUGHTER,
INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

29:20.049 --> 29:21.720
OKAY, BYE.

29:21.720 --> 29:23.933
BYE.

29:26.095 --> 29:28.938
HEY.
UM, HOW ARE YOU?

29:28.938 --> 29:31.600
UH, GOOD.
HOW'S DR. HERMAN? IS SHE GOOD?
IS EVERYTHING GOOD?

29:31.600 --> 29:33.732
YEAH, I MEAN, SHE'S KILLING
ME WITH BACK-TO-BACK
SURGERIES BUT --

29:33.732 --> 29:35.815
[ CHUCKLES ]
YEAH, AND AMELIA'S PLAN?
YOU GOOD WITH THAT?

29:35.815 --> 29:38.197
CALLIE, WHAT ARE YOU --
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT?

29:38.197 --> 29:39.989
I'M NOT --
I'M JUST CHECKING IN, OKAY?

29:39.989 --> 29:44.243
I'M JUST...SEEING HOW YOU ARE
AND, UH, HOW, UM...

29:44.243 --> 29:46.035
CALLIE?
WELL, IT JUST SEEMS LIKE

29:46.035 --> 29:47.997
YOU AND DR. HERMAN ARE GETTING
ALONG REALLY, REALLY WELL,

29:47.997 --> 29:50.039
AND YOU USED TO COMPLAIN
THAT SHE WAS KILLING YOU,

29:50.039 --> 29:51.580
BUT NOW YOU'RE HAPPY
THAT SHE'S KILLING YOU,

29:51.580 --> 29:53.212
AND IT SEEMS LIKE YOU
REALLY, REALLY LIKE HER.

29:53.212 --> 29:55.214
I DO. [ CHUCKLES ]
ACTUALLY, I DO. SHE'S GREAT.

29:55.214 --> 29:57.216
SHE'S --
I MEAN, SHE'S AMAZING.
AND SHE'S SICK.

29:57.216 --> 29:59.718
SO, I-I WORRY.
AMELIA'S GOT IT COVERED.

29:59.718 --> 30:02.051
SHE'S GONNA BE FINE.
I-I WORRY ABOUT YOU.

30:02.051 --> 30:03.472
I KNOW I SHOULDN'T.

30:03.472 --> 30:06.725
I KNOW IT'S NONE OF MY BUSINESS,
BUT, UH, OLD HABITS.

30:06.725 --> 30:09.228
WELL, THAT'S, UM...

30:09.228 --> 30:10.349
THANKS.

30:10.349 --> 30:12.271
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES, VIBRATES ]

30:12.271 --> 30:14.603
OH, I-I GOT TO GO.
OKAY, OKAY.

30:14.603 --> 30:15.644
Man:
WOW, THAT'S TALL.

30:15.644 --> 30:17.606
Woman:
YEAH. REALLY BIG.

30:21.110 --> 30:23.993
JUST SO YOU KNOW,
THE AUDITORIUM IS PACKED.

30:23.993 --> 30:26.325
THE FIRE MARSHALL ACTUALLY
MADE ME MOVE A BUNCH OF PEOPLE

30:26.325 --> 30:27.446
OUT TO AN OVERFLOW ROOM.

30:30.209 --> 30:31.911
AMELIA.

30:31.911 --> 30:33.622
JUST GIVE ME A MINUTE.

30:33.622 --> 30:35.004
AMELIA.
SHH!

30:35.004 --> 30:36.255
HANG ON.

30:39.418 --> 30:41.170
YOU CAN TALK TO ME.

30:41.170 --> 30:43.132
YOU'RE WOUND
PRETTY TIGHT.

30:43.132 --> 30:46.555
I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW
YOU CAN TALK TO ME.

30:48.227 --> 30:49.348
[ SIGHS ]

30:51.230 --> 30:53.732
MY WHOLE CAREER, I HAVE BEEN
THE OTHER DR. SHEPHERD.

30:55.274 --> 30:59.478
HE'S THE REAL ONE.
I'M THE OTHER ONE.

30:59.478 --> 31:03.362
RIGHT NOW, THIS PLAN OF MINE
IS THEORETICAL.

31:03.362 --> 31:05.034
IT'S JUST TALK.

31:05.034 --> 31:06.195
BUT AT SOME POINT,

31:06.195 --> 31:08.197
I AM GOING TO SLICE INTO
DR. HERMAN'S BRAIN,

31:08.197 --> 31:11.120
AND I HAVE
THIS SICK FEELING

31:11.120 --> 31:14.163
THAT WHEN I FACE
THAT TUMOR,

31:14.163 --> 31:18.998
I WILL DISCOVER THAT I AM NOT
JUST THE OTHER DR. SHEPHERD...

31:22.211 --> 31:25.054
...I'M THE WRONG
DR. SHEPHERD.

31:25.054 --> 31:27.806
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

31:31.470 --> 31:33.222
HEY.

31:33.222 --> 31:36.275
911?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

31:39.108 --> 31:41.230
LOOK, I KNOW YOU'VE
BEEN HAVING ME TAKE
THE LEAD SO I CAN LEARN,

31:41.230 --> 31:42.571
BUT YOU NEED
TO HANDLE THIS CASE.

31:42.571 --> 31:44.023
WHY WOULD I DO THAT?
BECAUSE IT'S EMERGENT,

31:44.023 --> 31:45.824
AND I'VE NEVER TRIED
CUTTING UMBILICAL BANDS.

31:45.824 --> 31:47.446
FIRST TIME
FOR EVERYTHING.
WELL -- [ SIGHS ]

31:47.446 --> 31:48.867
LISTEN TO ME, OKAY?

31:48.867 --> 31:50.199
I'M NOT READY
TO TAKE THIS OVER YET.

31:50.199 --> 31:51.740
DOESN'T MATTER.

31:51.740 --> 31:53.912
STOP! STOP!

31:53.912 --> 31:56.295
YOU -- [ STAMMERS ]
YOU'RE NOT HEARING ME.

31:56.295 --> 31:57.916
IT DOES MATTER.
I'M NOT READY.

31:57.916 --> 31:59.959
AND YOU THINK I AM?

31:59.959 --> 32:02.211
YOU THINK
THIS IS EASY FOR ME?

32:02.211 --> 32:03.422
YOU THINK I'M READY?

32:03.422 --> 32:08.007
I WAS FINE.
I GOT FINE WITH DYING.

32:08.007 --> 32:10.349
AND THEN YOU INFECTED ME
WITH YOUR STUPID --

32:10.349 --> 32:14.013
WITH SHEPHERD AND HER PLAN
AND YOUR STUPID HOPE.

32:14.013 --> 32:16.935
[ Voice breaking ]
AND NOW IT'S HARDER THAN EVER

32:16.935 --> 32:20.019
TO HAND ALL THIS OVER.

32:20.019 --> 32:21.480
I DON'T WANT TO.

32:21.480 --> 32:24.023
I'M SCARED TO.

32:24.023 --> 32:26.275
AND [SIGHS] I'M SCARED
TO LET GO OF IT,

32:26.275 --> 32:29.698
AND IT'S ALL
YOUR FAULT, SO...

32:29.698 --> 32:32.571
I THINK THE VERY LEAST
YOU COULD DO IS DESERVE IT.

32:32.571 --> 32:35.534
TAKE OVER, DO WELL,
MAKE ME NOT REGRET IT.

32:35.534 --> 32:36.745
CAN YOU DO THAT?

32:37.836 --> 32:39.208
PLEASE?

32:40.039 --> 32:41.710
Amelia:
THIS IS THE PART

32:41.710 --> 32:44.213
WHERE THINGS
GET A LITTLE FAST AND FURIOUS.

32:44.213 --> 32:47.216
IT IS ARGUABLY
THE MOST DANGEROUS,

32:47.216 --> 32:50.889
MOST PRECARIOUS
PORTION OF THE OPERATION.

32:50.889 --> 32:53.802
IT ALSO NEEDS
TO HAPPEN THE FASTEST.

32:53.802 --> 32:57.806
EVERY STEP,
EVERY MOVE BEFORE THIS

32:57.806 --> 32:59.728
HAS LAID THE GROUNDWORK
FOR THIS VERY MOMENT,

32:59.728 --> 33:03.022
THE MOMENT WHERE I PLACE
THE RADIOACTIVE SEEDS.

33:03.022 --> 33:04.863
IT REQUIRES PRECISION...

33:04.863 --> 33:07.066
I JUST NEED TO SLIP
THESE SHEARS UNDER THE BAND.

33:07.066 --> 33:09.448
...AND ACCURACY AND SPEED --

33:09.448 --> 33:12.111
THINGS THAT DO NOT
GO TOGETHER WELL.

33:12.111 --> 33:13.742
[ SIGHS ]
I CAN'T GET THE LAST BAND.

33:13.742 --> 33:15.284
THIS GRIP'S
NOT FLEXIBLE ENOUGH.

33:15.284 --> 33:17.166
Dr. Herman: CAN YOU
COAX IT THROUGH?

33:17.166 --> 33:19.878
MM. IT'S NOT -- NO.
IT WON'T GIVE.

33:19.878 --> 33:21.830
YOU HAVE TO CUT
THAT LAST BAND.
I KNOW.

33:21.830 --> 33:24.623
HAVE YOU TRIED
A SMALLER SCISSOR?
MM. IT'S NOT
THE PROBLEM.

33:24.623 --> 33:28.257
IMAGINE PICKING UP
LITTLE GRAINS OF SALT

33:28.257 --> 33:30.089
WHILE WEARING OVEN MITTS.

33:30.089 --> 33:33.892
THAT IS WHAT I'M DOING
INSIDE SOMEBODY'S BRAIN.

33:33.892 --> 33:35.684
HAND ME A GLOVE.
WHAT?

33:35.684 --> 33:37.306
SOMEBODY HAND ME A GLOVE.
SCISSORS.

33:37.306 --> 33:39.728
THERE'S THIS THING
THAT WE USED TO DO IN PEDS.

33:39.728 --> 33:41.019
I THINK IT'LL WORK.

33:41.019 --> 33:42.811
I JUST NEED
A MORE FLEXIBLE OPENING,

33:42.811 --> 33:44.193
AND I CAN MAKE IT
OUT OF A GLOVE.

33:44.193 --> 33:45.644
THAT'S NOT
IN MY NOTES, ROBBINS.

33:54.032 --> 33:55.364
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

33:57.536 --> 34:00.419
ARE YOU SERIOUS?
IT'S GONNA WORK.

34:00.419 --> 34:03.212
BUT ONCE I DO IT,

34:03.212 --> 34:07.126
ONCE I PLACE
THE FINAL SEED,

34:07.126 --> 34:09.468
WELL...

34:09.468 --> 34:11.630
IT'S SMOOTH SAILING.

34:11.630 --> 34:13.432
HA! DID YOU SEE THAT?!

34:13.432 --> 34:17.136
IT WORKED! IT -- IT --
IT ABSOLUTELY WORKED!

34:20.139 --> 34:22.521
'NIGHT, 'NIGHT,
TUMOR BABY.

34:22.521 --> 34:25.854
IT HAS BEEN LOVELY,

34:25.854 --> 34:27.186
BUT WE ARE DONE.

34:27.186 --> 34:30.949
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

34:37.826 --> 34:41.120
Amelia: I'D LIKE TO OPEN THINGS
UP TO A FEW QUESTIONS.

34:41.120 --> 34:42.581
YES.

34:42.581 --> 34:44.042
ARE YOU NERVOUS?

34:44.042 --> 34:46.545
UH...

34:46.545 --> 34:49.128
I'D BE CRAZY NOT TO BE.

34:49.128 --> 34:52.131
YES, OF COURSE I'M NERVOUS,
BUT I'M ALSO VERY EXCITED.

34:52.131 --> 34:54.423
THIS IS HISTORY.

34:54.423 --> 34:57.766
THIS SURGERY
WILL BE HISTORY.

34:57.766 --> 35:00.639
HOW COULD I
NOT BE EXCITED ABOUT THAT?

35:00.639 --> 35:04.353
[ SHEARS SNIP,
MONITOR BEEPING ]
EXCELLENT, EXCELLENT.

35:04.353 --> 35:06.145
YOU SHOULD BE
VERY PROUD OF YOURSELF.

35:06.145 --> 35:08.857
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:08.857 --> 35:10.028
CLOSE UP NOW.

35:10.028 --> 35:12.441
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

35:12.441 --> 35:15.404
Richard: WHAT YOU'RE DESCRIBING
IS SEVEN DIFFERENT SURGERIES

35:15.404 --> 35:19.037
ALL USING THE HARDEST TECHNIQUES
YOU'VE EVER TRIED.

35:19.037 --> 35:23.001
HOW LONG DO YOU ANTICIPATE THE
ENTIRE SURGERY ACTUALLY TAKING?

35:23.001 --> 35:25.164
18 HOURS...
[ AUDIENCE MURMURING ]

35:25.164 --> 35:26.875
...GIVE OR TAKE
SOME HOURS.

35:26.875 --> 35:27.746
[ LAUGHTER ]

35:27.746 --> 35:29.007
Jo:
UH, FOLLOW-UP QUESTION --

35:29.007 --> 35:31.510
DO YOU NEED A SECOND RESIDENT
ON THE CASE?

35:31.510 --> 35:35.013
UH, NOT UNLESS EDWARDS
IS PLANNING TO BAIL ON ME.

35:35.013 --> 35:36.885
YOU PLANNING
TO BAIL, EDWARDS?

35:36.885 --> 35:38.136
NO, MA'AM.

35:44.393 --> 35:46.685
YES, IN THE BACK.

35:46.685 --> 35:48.397
Callie:
WILL YOU HAVE HELP?

35:48.397 --> 35:51.190
UM...SORRY?

35:51.190 --> 35:52.691
WELL, I'M JUST, UH --

35:52.691 --> 35:54.773
WELL, ARE YOU GONNA BE DOING
THIS WHOLE SURGERY YOURSELF,

35:54.773 --> 35:56.575
OR IS DEREK --
UH, DR. SHEPHERD COMING?

35:56.575 --> 35:59.368
I'M -- I'M JUST --
I'M JUST ASKING.

35:59.368 --> 36:01.780
I MEAN, GIVEN EVERYTHING,
IS IT A GOOD IDEA?

36:01.780 --> 36:03.582
SHOULD YOU
BE DOING THIS YOURSELF?

36:03.582 --> 36:05.123
[ AUDIENCE MURMURS ]

36:05.123 --> 36:08.837
WELL, I AM, SO...

36:11.089 --> 36:12.461
NEXT QUESTION.

36:12.461 --> 36:14.213
[ INDISTINCT WHISPERING ]

36:20.429 --> 36:23.222
I NEED YOU TO SCAN ME.

36:23.222 --> 36:28.106
SOMETHING'S HAPPENING.
I'M EXPERIENCING SYMPTOMS --

36:28.106 --> 36:32.271
FUZZINESS AROUND THE EDGES,
A LITTLE LIKE, UH, BLINDERS,

36:32.271 --> 36:37.986
AND IT'S, UH, DARK -- DARKER
THAN IT SHOULD BE, I THINK.

36:40.489 --> 36:43.912
OKAY.

36:43.912 --> 36:46.415
LET'S GO.

37:02.341 --> 37:04.553
[ MACHINERY WHIRRING ]

37:09.938 --> 37:12.190
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

37:19.067 --> 37:21.029
[ SIGHS ]
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

37:21.029 --> 37:22.451
BAILEY?
WHERE'S DR. HERMAN?

37:22.451 --> 37:24.032
SHE STEPPED OUT.
WHAT DO YOU NEED?

37:24.032 --> 37:26.244
UH...IT'S
GLENDA CASTILLO.

37:28.867 --> 37:30.289
HEY, I NEED HERMAN
RIGHT NOW.

37:30.289 --> 37:31.960
GLENDA CASTILLO'S BABY
IS IN DISTRESS,

37:31.960 --> 37:33.422
AND GLENDA
IS SEVERELY HYPERTENSIVE,

37:33.422 --> 37:34.873
SHOWING SIGNS
OF HEART FAILURE.

37:34.873 --> 37:36.965
WE NEED TO OPERATE
ON HER IMMEDIATELY,

37:36.965 --> 37:38.967
SO IF YOU
COULD FINISH UP...

37:38.967 --> 37:40.258
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

37:40.258 --> 37:41.930
WHY ARE YOU
STANDING THERE? I--
ARIZONA.

37:47.055 --> 37:48.016
Oh, God.

37:49.558 --> 37:50.729
IT'S TIME.

37:50.729 --> 37:53.151
NOW?

37:57.155 --> 38:01.199
I'M GONNA GO...

38:01.199 --> 38:02.741
GET AN O.R. READY.

38:02.741 --> 38:04.823
OKAY.

38:04.823 --> 38:06.074
OKAY.

38:08.036 --> 38:09.408
YOU READY
F-FOR THIS?

38:12.250 --> 38:14.042
MM-HMM.

38:15.003 --> 38:16.214
A-AMELIA.

38:18.006 --> 38:19.838
I'LL GET AN O.R. PREPPED.

38:21.219 --> 38:23.051
YOU'LL INFORM
THE PATIENT?

38:29.638 --> 38:32.190
Dr. Herman:
OH. ROBBINS.

38:32.190 --> 38:33.642
[ GRUNTS ]
SURGERY'S ALL FINISHED?

38:33.642 --> 38:35.193
YEAH.

38:35.193 --> 38:37.486
[ SIGHS ]

38:37.486 --> 38:39.277
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

38:39.277 --> 38:41.239
I SEE.

38:41.239 --> 38:42.861
SHEPHERD'S
PREPPING THE O.R.?

38:42.861 --> 38:44.993
YES.

38:44.993 --> 38:46.204
IF I HAD TO GUESS,

38:46.204 --> 38:49.748
I'D SAY THE TUMOR'S
INVADED THE OPTIC CHIASM.

38:52.330 --> 38:54.212
AH.

38:54.212 --> 38:55.664
MY CHARIOT AWAITS.

38:58.166 --> 38:59.628
A LITTLE PRIVACY, GUYS?

39:02.961 --> 39:06.174
DID YOU, UH, NEED ME
FOR SOMETHING -- A PATIENT?

39:06.174 --> 39:07.766
UM, YEAH.

39:07.766 --> 39:09.347
GLENDA CASTILLO'S BABY
HAS HYDROPS.

39:09.347 --> 39:11.600
MOM IS MIRRORING,
AND SHE'S GOING INTO CHF.

39:11.600 --> 39:13.682
WOW.

39:13.682 --> 39:16.104
LOOKS LIKE A BIG DAY
FOR BOTH OF US.

39:16.104 --> 39:18.316
WHAT YOU NEED
TO DO FIRST

39:18.316 --> 39:21.279
IS TRY TO EMBOLIZE
THE VESSELS FETOSCOPICALLY.

39:21.279 --> 39:23.532
MAKE SURE HER BLOOD PRESSURE
IS STABILIZED.

39:23.532 --> 39:25.904
SHE HAS YOU.

39:25.904 --> 39:27.155
AMELIA HAS YOU.

39:27.155 --> 39:29.488
THIS IS THE POINT
WHERE YOU TRUST HER, OKAY?

39:29.488 --> 39:32.330
DON'T GO IN WITHOUT CHECKING
GLENDA'S PLATELET COUNTS

39:32.330 --> 39:33.492
AND CROSSMATCHING.

39:33.492 --> 39:36.254
THIS IS THE POINT
WHERE YOU TRUST HER, OKAY?

39:37.996 --> 39:40.048
ALL SET.

39:40.048 --> 39:41.630
DON'T LET GLENDA'S
PLATELET COUNT DROP BELOW --

39:41.630 --> 39:43.001
100. I KNOW.

39:43.001 --> 39:44.503
WILL YOU TIE ME?
YEAH.

39:46.134 --> 39:47.466
[ SIGHS ]

39:51.930 --> 39:54.312
[ BOTH BREATHE DEEPLY ]

39:54.312 --> 39:58.186
[ HOLLOW WOOD'S "SEASONS"
PLAYS ]

40:02.941 --> 40:05.193
[ SIGHS ]

40:11.119 --> 40:12.330
LET'S DO THIS.

40:38.146 --> 40:39.478
Dr. Herman:
I NEVER PLACED MUCH VALUE

40:39.478 --> 40:41.109
IN WONDERING
ABOUT AN AFTERLIFE.

40:41.109 --> 40:43.191
MY CONCERN
WAS ALWAYS THIS LIFE,

40:43.191 --> 40:44.943
WHAT WOULD I DO WITH IT?

40:44.943 --> 40:46.485
HOW WOULD I MAKE MY MARK?

40:46.485 --> 40:49.327
BE SURE, BE FAST. YOU DON'T HAVE
HALF THE TIME YOU IMAGINE.

40:49.327 --> 40:51.740
TRY TO ABLATE ALL THE VESSELS,
BUT DON'T WAIT TOO LONG.

40:51.740 --> 40:53.071
DON'T BE AFRAID
TO MAKE THAT CALL.

40:53.071 --> 40:55.033
IF SHE'S AWAKE, SHE'LL
TELL YOU FOR THE 15th TIME

40:55.033 --> 40:56.284
TO SAVE HER CHILD'S LIFE
BEFORE HERS.

40:56.284 --> 40:58.376
LISTEN TO HER,
LET HER SAY HER PIECE,

40:58.376 --> 41:01.039
THEN YOU DO
WHAT NEEDS TO BE DONE.
I DON'T THINK -- I DON'T --
I DON'T KNOW --

41:01.039 --> 41:02.501
[ SIGHS ] I DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN DO THIS.

41:02.501 --> 41:03.922
I CAN'T.
I CAN'T DO THIS.
YOU CAN.

41:03.922 --> 41:05.884
NICOLE.
YOU WILL.

41:07.255 --> 41:09.678
LET'S GET YOU
INSIDE NOW, OKAY?

41:09.678 --> 41:12.010
I WANTED
TO BREAK NEW GROUND.

41:12.010 --> 41:16.394
♪ LIGHT TURNED TO DARK ♪
I WANTED TO LEAVE A LEGACY.

41:16.394 --> 41:22.190
I WANTED MY LIFE,
MY BRAIN, MY EXISTENCE...

41:22.190 --> 41:24.653
♪ BUT DEATH
CAN'T TAKE YOU AWAY ♪

41:24.653 --> 41:27.155
...TO MEAN SOMETHING.

41:30.158 --> 41:32.070
♪ I'LL TAKE THESE MEMORIES ♪
[ AIR HISSING ]

41:32.070 --> 41:33.822
HEY, HEY, HEY,
YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE, OKAY?

41:33.822 --> 41:36.374
AMELIA'S GOT THIS.
YOU'VE GOT THIS.

41:36.374 --> 41:39.377
THE THING THAT I NEVER
REALLY THOUGHT ABOUT, THOUGH,

41:39.377 --> 41:42.040
THE THING I NEVER REALLY
WRAPPED MY BRAIN AROUND

41:42.040 --> 41:43.461
UNTIL NOW WAS...

41:43.461 --> 41:44.793
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

41:44.793 --> 41:46.625
♪ AND SAIL AWAY ♪

41:46.625 --> 41:47.836
WAIT, ROBBINS.

41:47.836 --> 41:49.297
NO.

41:49.297 --> 41:50.589
DON'T YOU DARE.

41:50.589 --> 41:52.430
DON'T YOU DARE
SAY IT, NICOLE.

41:52.430 --> 41:55.473
...IN ORDER TO DO THAT,
IN ORDER TO BE REMEMBERED,

41:55.473 --> 41:59.227
IN ORDER TO LEAVE
SOMETHING SIGNIFICANT BEHIND...

41:59.227 --> 42:00.729
TIME TO GO.

42:14.653 --> 42:16.154
[ AIR HISSING ]

42:16.154 --> 42:18.577
...YOU HAVE TO LEAVE.
